  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Category
    This interface declares that every Category of nonconformance has an type.

    Categorize
    Class used to categorize the nonconformances discovered into the SUT.

    Class used to set the category name of each nonconformance revealed by the Detect module.

    Class used to set the cause name of each nonconformance revealed by the Detect module.
    Constraint
    An category of nonconformance, the Constraint Error.
    Evaluation
    An category of nonconformance, the Evaluation Error.
    Examinator
    Class used to do some operations on the AST that we use to determinate which is the likely cause for a nonconformance.
    Invariant

    Nonconformance

    Postcondition

    An category of nonconformance, the Precondition Error.
